    Objects map[string]*InferredObject  // Lowercase object name → object
}
Inference Algorithms
SOQL-Based Inference
Entry Point: 

InferFromSOQL(soql string)

Algorithm:

Extract object name from FROM clause via regex: FROM\s+(\w+)
Extract SELECT fields via regex: SELECT\s+(.+?)\s+FROM
Split fields by comma (handling nested subquery parens)
For each field:
If contains .: Parse as parent traversal (see below)
Else: Infer type from field name heuristics
Extract WHERE clause fields:
Pattern 1: Comparison operators (=, !=, <, >, <=, >=)
Pattern 2: IN operator (Status IN (...))
Pattern 3: LIKE operator (Name LIKE 'Acme%')
Pattern 4: INCLUDES operator (Industry INCLUDES (...))
Parent Traversal Example:

Query: SELECT Account.Owner.Name FROM Contact
Inference:
  - Contact has AccountId (lookup to Account), confidence 85
  - Account has OwnerId (lookup to User), confidence 85
  - User has Name (String), confidence 75
Algorithm for Parent Traversal:

func inferParentTraversal(baseObject, path string) {
    parts := strings.Split(path, ".")  // ["Account", "Owner", "Name"]
    currentObject := baseObject        // "Contact"
    
    for i := 0; i < len(parts)-1; i++ {
        relationName := parts[i]  // "Account", then "Owner"
        fieldName := relationName + "Id"  // "AccountId", "OwnerId"
        targetObject := inferObjectFromRelation(relationName)
        
        addFieldWithReference(currentObject, fieldName, "Id", 
            targetObject, relationName, "SOQL", 85)
        
        currentObject = targetObject
    }
    
    finalField := parts[len(parts)-1]  // "Name"
    addField(currentObject, finalField, inferType(finalField), "SOQL", 75)
}
DML-Based Inference
Entry Point: 

InferFromDML(objectName string, fieldAssignments map[string]string)

Algorithm:

Extract object type from DML target (e.g., insert acc → "Account")
Extract field assignments from SObject instance:
for fieldName, fieldValue := range recordFields {
    fieldType := inferTypeFromValue(fieldValue)
    addField(objectName, fieldName, fieldType, "DML", 70)
}
Type inference from literal values:
"true" or "false" → Boolean
Numeric string → Integer or Decimal
Default → String
