Type Declaration Inference
Entry Point: 

InferFromTypeDeclaration(typeName string)

Algorithm:

Check for generic types: List<\w+>, Map<\w+,\s*(\w+)>, Set<\w+>
Extract SObject name from generic
Filter out primitives (String, Integer, Boolean, etc.)
Create or retrieve inferred object with low confidence (type decl alone doesn't reveal fields)
Examples:

List<Account> → Account object exists
Map<Id, Contact> → Contact object exists
Set<Opportunity> → Opportunity object exists
