Confidence Scoring
Confidence scores indicate reliability of inference (0-100):

Score	Meaning
95	Maximum confidence (repeated sightings)
85	High confidence (parent traversal lookups)
80	High confidence (SOQL SELECT fields)
75	Medium-high (parent traversal final fields)
70	Medium (DML field assignments)
60	Lower (WHERE clause fields - type unknown)
50	Low (field access without context)
Confidence Boosting:

Each repeated field sighting adds +10 confidence (max 95)
Type refinement: if field type changes from "unknown" to concrete type, update type and boost confidence
if existing.Type == fieldType || existing.Type == "unknown" {
    existing.Confidence = min(95, max(existing.Confidence, confidence) + 10)
    if existing.Type == "unknown" && fieldType != "unknown" {
        existing.Type = fieldType
    }
}
Type Inference Heuristics
Field Name Patterns:

func inferTypeFromContext(fieldName string) string {
    lower := strings.ToLower(fieldName)
    
    if strings.HasSuffix(lower, "id") { return "Id" }
    if strings.HasSuffix(lower, "date") { return "Date" }
    if strings.Contains(lower, "datetime") { return "Datetime" }
    if strings.HasPrefix(lower, "is") || strings.HasPrefix(lower, "has") { 
        return "Boolean" 
    }
    if strings.Contains(lower, "amount") || strings.Contains(lower, "price") { 
        return "Decimal" 
    }
    if strings.Contains(lower, "count") || strings.Contains(lower, "number") { 
        return "Integer" 
    }
    
    return "String"  // Default
}
Metadata Integration
Priority: XML Metadata > Inferred Schema

Merge Process:

func MergeWithInferredSchema(engine *SchemaInferenceEngine) {
    for objectName, inferredObj := range engine.Objects {
        sobj := metadata.GetSObjectDef(objectName)
        if sobj == nil {
            // Object doesn't exist - create from inferred
            metadata.addInferredObject(inferredObj)
        } else {
            // Merge fields: only add if not in XML
            for fieldName, inferredField := range inferredObj.Fields {
                if !sobj.hasField(fieldName) {
                    sobj.addInferredField(inferredField)
                }
                // If field exists in XML, XML wins
            }
        }
    }
}
